%description:
Regression test for RSVP-TE Hello-based failure detection and permanent-path retry
(RFC 2205 Section 3.1, RFC 3209 Section 4.7), using the shipped
examples/mpls/testte_failure network (RSVPTE4) and its own default scenario as-is: LSR4
(a transit hop on the tunnel's single, explicitly-routed path LSR1->LSR2->LSR4->LSR5) is
shut down at t=2s and restarted at t=4s.

Asserted, in order:
  1. the shutdown fires;
  2. LSR2 (LSR4's neighbor on the path) detects the dead adjacency via Hello timeout
     (RsvpTe::processHELLO_TIMEOUT) and raises a PathErr for the affected PSB -- the
     only caller of sendPathErrorMessage(..., PATH_ERR_NEXTHOP_FAILED) in this model,
     so "error reached ingress router" below is necessarily that error code even
     though RsvpTe.cc never prints the symbolic constant itself;
  3. the PathErr reaches the ingress (LSR1), which tears down the failed path and,
     because the session is marked <permanent>true</permanent>, schedules a retry;
  4. the startup fires;
  5. the retried path is (re-)established -- RsvpTe::commitResv's PATH_CREATED
     notification fires again at the ingress.

Deviation from a natural first guess: this network's session route is a fully
explicit, hand-written ERO (LSR1_rsvp.xml lists every hop), not a CSPF-computed one,
so the retry keeps re-trying the SAME route rather than routing around LSR4 -- it
fails again once (observable as a second "error reached ingress router" before t=4s)
and only succeeds once LSR4 itself restarts. That is expected behavior for an
explicitly-routed session in this codebase (CSPF-based rerouting, if present at all,
is a different workstream's feature), not a bug, so this test asserts recovery via
LSR4's own restart rather than an alternate path.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: test.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../examples;../../../../src
network = inet.examples.mpls.testte_failure.RSVPTE4
sim-time-limit = 6s
total-stack = 64MiB
record-vector-results = false
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-event-banners = false
**.LSR*.rsvp.cmdenv-log-level = info
**.scenarioManager.cmdenv-log-level = info
**.cmdenv-log-level = off

**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpBasicApp"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].destPort = 100
**.host1.app[0].messageLength = 128 bytes
**.host1.app[0].sendInterval = 0.01s
**.host1.app[0].destAddresses = "host3"

**.host3.numApps = 1
**.host3.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host3.app[0].localPort = 100

**.host1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/host1.rt"
**.host2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/host2.rt"
**.host3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/host3.rt"
**.host4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/host4.rt"
**.host5.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/host5.rt"

**.LSR1.classifier.config = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR1_fec.xml")
**.LSR1.rsvp.traffic = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR1_rsvp.xml")

**.LSR*.rsvp.helloInterval = 0.2s
**.LSR*.rsvp.helloTimeout = 0.5s

**.LSR1.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR1.rt"
**.LSR2.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR2.rt"
**.LSR3.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR3.rt"
**.LSR4.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR4.rt"
**.LSR5.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR5.rt"
**.LSR6.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR6.rt"
**.LSR7.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/LSR7.rt"

**.ppp[*].queue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.ppp[*].queue.packetCapacity = 10

*.*.hasStatus = true
**.scenarioManager.script = xmldoc("../../../../examples/mpls/testte_failure/scenario.xml")

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# ordered: LSR4 shuts down -> LSR2 detects the dead Hello adjacency -> the PathErr
%# reaches the ingress -> LSR4 restarts -> the retried path is established again
%contains-regex: stdout
processing <shutdown> command\.\.\.
.*
hello timeout, considering .* failed
.*
error reached ingress router
.*
processing <startup> command\.\.\.
.*
Path successfully established
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
